244
00:19:03,421 --> 00:19:06,522
atop the corpses of thy brethren, literally,

245
00:19:07,122 --> 00:19:12,043
giving us the feeling of what it would be like to live inside of King Diamond's Abigail album.

246
00:19:12,983 --> 00:19:15,164
When we're building these sorts of metal worlds,

247
00:19:16,364 --> 00:19:21,946
at the highest level, there are four traits or attributes that define a metal world.

248
00:19:22,606 --> 00:19:23,226
The sublime...

249
00:19:24,059 --> 00:19:27,581
the gothic, the weird, and the grimdark.

250
00:19:28,831 --> 00:19:35,853
The sublime refers to an aesthetic experience beyond human comprehension, a vision of natural

251
00:19:35,913 --> 00:19:39,894
and cosmic grandeur in which human beings are insignificant.

252
00:19:40,214 --> 00:19:44,795
Looking down over the edge of that canyon, not only does it dwarf the man looking down

253
00:19:44,835 --> 00:19:51,157
into it, but a single step would kill him, and in that danger is the power of the sublime.

254
00:19:51,837 --> 00:19:58,398
The gothic, featuring wild landscapes, ruined architecture, supernatural horror.

255
00:20:00,059 --> 00:20:05,803
Ravenloft is metal, because Ravenloft is gothic, directly derived from the gothic.

256
00:20:05,883 --> 00:20:10,367
It's the gothic pocket dimension of the Dungeons and Dragons universe.

257
00:20:11,628 --> 00:20:18,533
Innistrad is metal, because its cards are a machine for generatively combining gothic

258
00:20:18,653 --> 00:20:21,675
elements in the Magic the Gathering multiverse.

259
00:20:22,656 --> 00:20:24,797
The Shire is not metal.

260
00:20:30,192 --> 00:20:33,002
But ringwraiths are metal as fuck.

261
00:20:37,224 --> 00:20:46,311
Michael Moorcock fused together the traits of epic fantasy with those of weird fiction

262
00:20:46,471 --> 00:20:53,215
in his Elric saga, producing a world that is decadent, psychedelic, mind-warping.

263
00:20:53,656 --> 00:20:59,500
In the words of Alan Moore, Elric's Melnibony is warped with a touch of fractal horrors

264
00:20:59,940 --> 00:21:02,962
and fluoresces with toxic elf repellent.

265
00:21:04,063 --> 00:21:05,384
Melnibony is metal.

266
00:21:06,554 --> 00:21:09,876
And Warhammer 40K, it's very metal.

267
00:21:11,016 --> 00:21:14,317
It is, its motto is that in the grim darkness

268
00:21:14,377 --> 00:21:16,698
of the far future, there is only war.

269
00:21:17,439 --> 00:21:20,420
And out of this motto comes the aesthetic trait

270
00:21:20,760 --> 00:21:25,202
of grimdark and an entire anti-Tolkien movement

271
00:21:25,262 --> 00:21:27,443
of fantasy from George R.R. Martin

272
00:21:27,963 --> 00:21:31,205
to Mark Lawrence's Broken Empire series.

273
00:21:31,845 --> 00:21:35,426
And when we fuse these aspects of metal worlds together,

274
00:21:36,814 --> 00:21:46,180
we get Yharnam in Bloodborne, which is gothic, grimdark, weird, and sublimely metal.

275
00:21:47,307 --> 00:21:51,150
We could take a cue here from Dan Pinchbeck's excellent book on doom,

276
00:21:51,570 --> 00:21:55,513
which he titled Scary Dark Fast, to suggest that all three of those words

277
00:21:55,873 --> 00:21:59,416
become one word, because doom is characterized

278
00:21:59,836 --> 00:22:03,699
by one unified experience that fuses all of those traits.

279
00:22:04,340 --> 00:22:06,781
We might say, taking a page from Pinchbeck,

280
00:22:07,442 --> 00:22:10,144
that metal is defined by gothic weird sublime.

281
00:22:11,221 --> 00:22:15,467
And this is certainly true at the macro level of the overall world,

282
00:22:16,048 --> 00:22:21,196
but it's also true at the micro level, at the level of level design.

283
00:22:22,629 --> 00:22:27,351
Metal level design is a surreal non-Euclidean nightmare.

284
00:22:28,071 --> 00:22:31,153
It is the castle and the inverted castle

285
00:22:31,633 --> 00:22:33,394
of Castlevania Symphony of the Night,

286
00:22:33,895 --> 00:22:36,416
threatening always to topple over on itself

287
00:22:36,876 --> 00:22:38,957
in its involuted, twisting hallways,

288
00:22:39,458 --> 00:22:42,960
or the Winchester house-like stairways to nowhere

289
00:22:43,440 --> 00:22:47,542
in the second level of the Tower of Latria from Demon's Souls.

290
00:22:48,463 --> 00:22:49,643
Metal level design.

291
00:22:50,665 --> 00:22:58,670
is the architecture of madness. Always different, yet somehow always the same, as in the many

292
00:22:58,770 --> 00:23:05,574
iterations of Castle Ravenloft, its spires corkscrewing off into the void.

293
00:23:07,856 --> 00:23:14,060
